<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
We all know that there are issues betwen the pure melee and the hybrids and that a happy contimuim may not be reached, but i agree a min damage for a warrior would be a great thing. I dont really care if a monk or other class outdamages me, all I am concerned about in a grp situation is that I take the hits and no one else. As a warrior I take pride in teh amount of damage I absorb and fell comforted by the fact that one of the low ac group mates didnt just take that 100+ hit I did with my great ac. sure we all want to be able to do more damge, but I don't think that is the problem wiht warriors right now. The problem is in the equipment we get. Rogues, warriors, and monks really rely on the equipment they have but some of the equipment we get is down right disguting. <BR>But the biggest problem is really getting nothing between 35 and 60 other than more hp, I think a good skill or discipline( which from my experience really dont seem that great) would be a skill that focuses the current enemies attention on us, sort of a challange to what ever monster we are fighting. They are mad at us we are mad at them,hence we fight.<BR>I also like what I read about Honor and fear for a warrior, I really dislike having to run like a ninny from a greenie as it beats me down on a corpse run. A sort of herois stature should accompany the warrior and possibly all quests. Sort of maybe faction based and or quest based. I can see that doing a certain quest might raise my skill in "heroics" by 1, thus letting every mob know that wow this warrior is making a name for themselves. Hmm a big hero we should be scared. On the contrary maybe some mobs are out for the chalange and will attack those with the higher heroics rating. <BR>Just some ideas, I have many more, not just for warriors only, so please dont flame me.<BR>If you can flame my ideas and do so inteligentaly and logically.
</FONT>
