<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Faintheart><P>The reason for this is: Large armor weighs more because it's a lot larger. Look at it proportionally:<P>Haflings are about 3ft. tall, maybe a bit less, and rather skinny. Ogres are very tall, and wide. if you stack them up proportionally, I think <P>1 Ogre = 6 Haflings (maybe more).<P>SO, since the armor has to cover a lot more, and is far larger, it should weigh more. Hell, based on that comparison, all Ogre armor should weigh about 6 times (or more) that of a hafling.
</FONT>
