<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I don't know about all that honor stuff, or about the race skills. I agree that the races really don't matter in the long run, and that it's kinda weird that a gnome can go toe to toe with a ogre. But if you think about it that the gnome is small and dodges more and hits more where as the ogre has a hard time hitting something small but when he does.... well it's over.<P>When I think of a warrior, I think of someone who will do anything and everything to win the fight, short of magic and such. Warriors should get more attack skills. Not like monks Flying kick and dragon punch. But such like Headbutt, and Poke to the Eyes. Dirty tricks that you would use. Some ideas of mine:<P>Headbutt: Low damage, chance to stun, auto interupt, fast recycle, and damage to the warrior if skill is low. (Could add bounuses if you have certain helmets)<P>Poke to the Eyes: Blind, low damage, interupt.<P>Trip: No damage, interup, root, stun.<P>Knee to the Groin: High damage interput<P>Tackel: Roots you and target, huge agro, some damage.<P>Those are some of my ideas. I play a warrior for the image. I am an Ogre. I use 2hs. I am big and I carry a big stick. Honor.... forget that, I will do anything to kill the mob. In a group I don't care if I do the most damage, I care if I take the most damage, and I take pride in finishing the mob.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
  IP: <A HREF="http://206.135.232.126/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_ip&f=288&t=000037&reply_num=000011">Logged</A>
</FONT>
</td></tr>
